[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "acdac8596aac3387a0f7630b590d0d9b7e8a80c065c3dd1a0d31c171dd23471d"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{You would have opened 1NT but South beat you to it. You cannot double for penalties when you use DONT, so you pass.

Partner bids 2\S in the balancing seat.  

The 2\S bid shows a weak hand, with more strength partner would have first doubled, then bid 2\S.

Still, you know he has a 6-card suit and you also know that every finesse is going to work. You either bid 3\S or 4\S. Be bold.}

